Step 1: Installing Apache on Ubuntu 18.04
        Start terminal by Pressing Ctrl + Alt + T
        sudo apt update 
        sudo apt install apache2
        
        Checking Webservice status 
        sudo systemctl status apache2
Step 2 : Adding management tools
          sudo systemctl status apache2
          sudo systemctl stop apache2
          sudo systemctl start apache2
          sudo systemctl restart apache2
          sudo systemctl reload apache2
          sudo systemctl enable apache2
          sudo systemctl disable apache2
Step 3 : Allowing Port 
         sudo ufw allow 80/tcp
         sudo ufw allow 443/tcp
         sudo ufw  reload
Step 4 : Goto Local Host in web browser

Heyyyy,Mate you have successfully installed Apache Server in your Machine.


         
        
        
        
